7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Article Forge and Rytr share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Seo Tools, Multilingual, Api Access. On the other hand, Rytr uniquely offers Short Form and Templates and Tone Control and Plagiarism Check and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Article Forge holds an overall score of 4/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Rytr scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Rytr comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Article Forge begins at $27/mo. Rytr stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Article Forge requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
